Quantum physics is radically different to the world as Newton’s laws described it, both conceptually and mathematically. Einstein very uneasy with the theory he helped found, leading him to believe that it was incomplete. This phenomena is Entanglement or spooky action of an atom.
Entanglement is a physical phenomenon which occurs when pairs or groups of particles are generate, interact, or share spatial proximity.
Measurements of physical properties such as
position,
momentum,
spin,
and polarization
The particles at the time of measurement may be separated by arbitrarily large distances.
It appears that one particle of an entangled pair “knows” what measurement has been performed on the other. Even though there is no known means for such information to be communicated between the particles.
But Entanglement had some issues
Imagine you have 2 identical bags. You put red color ball in one bag and blue color ball in the other. Now , its impossible to tell which bag contains blue ball and which one contains red ball. You randomly select a bag and sent it on moon.
Now when you will open the bag which is with you you will immediately know which color ball is in the the other bag. But this seemed to violate the speed limit on the transmission of information implicit in the theory of relativity.
