Special relativity made the case for locality even stronger, as it introduced the cosmic speed limit, the speed of light. Nothing can propagate faster than light, be it a particle or information about someone measuring your entangled partner photon. Einstein did not like non-locality in physics, and dubbed this effect as “spooky action at a distance”.
In 1935 Einstein, Boris Podolsky and Nathan Rosen published paper,“Can Quantum-Mechanical Description of Physical Reality Be Considered Complete?”. According it, Entanglement can not cause a measurement on one particle to affect another further away. Instead, particles actually have well determined positions, velocities…
