But it again poses some questions -
“Was quantum mechanics an incomplete description of reality?”
However, in 1964 John Bell published a paper titled “On the Einstein Podolosky Rosen Paradox” . He examined the consequences of hidden variable theories, as they had become known.
His work found that such a theory could not be constructed and still give predictions consistent with quantum mechanics. In fact, he found out that hidden variable theories would even be in contradiction with special relativity.
Since then, experiments have been in agreement with both the predictions of Bell’s work and those of quantum mechanics. Among those predictions is quantum entanglement, most important resource of the rising fields of quantum information and computing.